---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'evacuation-types', text: 'Types of Evacuation Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'when-needed', text: 'When You Might Need Evacuation', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Medical Evacuation Guide', href: '/guides/medical-evacuation-coverage' },
  { title: 'High-Risk Destinations', href: '/guides/high-risk-destinations' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', cigna: 'Unlimited', bupa: 'Unlimited', allianz: 'Up to €1M' },
  { feature: 'Repatriation', cigna: 'Included', bupa: 'Included', allianz: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'Assistance Network', cigna: 'Own network', bupa: 'Partner network', allianz: 'Partner network' },
  { feature: 'Response Time', cigna: 'Fastest', bupa: 'Fast', allianz: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Security Evacuation', cigna: 'Add-on', bupa: 'Add-on', allianz: 'Add-on' },
  { feature: 'Air Ambulance', cigna: 'Included', bupa: 'Included', allianz: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'Family Transport', cigna: 'Included', bupa: 'Included', allianz: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Best For', cigna: 'Remote locations', bupa: 'Premium service', allianz: 'Standard needs' },
];

const evacuationTypesColumns = [
  { key: 'type', header: 'Type' },
  { key: 'description', header: 'What It Covers' },
  { key: 'cost', header: 'Typical Cost' },
];

const evacuationTypesRows = [
  { type: 'Ground Ambulance', description: 'Transport to nearest hospital', cost: '$500-5,000' },
  { type: 'Air Ambulance (Regional)', description: 'Helicopter or plane within region', cost: '$25,000-75,000' },
  { type: 'Air Ambulance (International)', description: 'Medical jet to another country', cost: '$100,000-300,000' },
  { type: 'Repatriation', description: 'Transport home for treatment', cost: '$50,000-200,000' },
  { type: 'Mortal Remains', description: 'Body repatriation if deceased', cost: '$10,000-25,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Best Medical Evacuation Coverage 2026"
  description="Compare medical evacuation and emergency transport coverage from Cigna, Bupa, and Allianz. Air ambulance, repatriation, and security evacuation for expats abroad."
  headline="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Medical Evacuation Compared"
  subheadline="When you need emergency transport, quality matters. Here's how the three major insurers handle medical evacuation and repatriation."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Evacuation</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Own assistance network. Fastest response. Unlimited evacuation. Best for remote or risky locations.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Premium Service</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Excellent coordination. Unlimited coverage. Strong partner network. Premium support during crisis.</p>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Good Coverage</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">€1M evacuation limit (usually sufficient). Solid assistance. Best value with good protection.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    All three insurers include medical evacuation, but quality differs. Cigna has its own assistance network for fastest response. Bupa offers premium coordination through partners. Allianz provides solid coverage at better prices. If you're in remote or high-risk areas, evacuation quality matters more than price.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Own Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Fastest Response</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Unlimited</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global stands out with its own global assistance network—not outsourced to partners. This means faster response times and tighter coordination in emergencies. For expats in Africa, remote Asia, or other challenging locations, Cigna's evacuation capabilities are the gold standard.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Evacuation strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Own 24/7 assistance network (not outsourced)</li>
    <li>Fastest response and coordination times</li>
    <li>Unlimited medical evacuation coverage</li>
    <li>Air ambulance included (international medical jets)</li>
    <li>Family member transport included</li>
    <li>Repatriation to home country covered</li>
    <li>Security evacuation add-on available</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive overall</li>
    <li>Security evacuation not included by default</li>
    <li>Premium may exceed needs for low-risk destinations</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Expats in Africa, remote Asia, developing countries. Those in high-risk locations. Anyone who wants the best evacuation support regardless of cost.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="bupa-global">Bupa Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Premium Service</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Strong Partners</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Unlimited</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Bupa Global offers excellent evacuation through premium partner networks. While not their own operation like Cigna, Bupa's partnerships with top assistance providers mean reliable, high-quality evacuation coordination. Premium customer service during a crisis.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Evacuation strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Unlimited medical evacuation</li>
    <li>Premium partner assistance network</li>
    <li>Excellent crisis support and coordination</li>
    <li>Air ambulance included</li>
    <li>Family member transport included</li>
    <li>Repatriation covered</li>
    <li>Strong claims support during evacuation</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Partner network (not own operation)</li>
    <li>Most expensive option</li>
    <li>Response may be slightly slower than Cigna in remote areas</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Expats who want premium service during any emergency. Those who value customer support in crisis situations. Long-term expats wanting lifetime renewal protection.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">€1M Coverage</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Solid Support</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care provides solid evacuation coverage at better prices than Cigna or Bupa. The €1M evacuation limit is sufficient for the vast majority of situations. For expats in moderate-risk locations, Allianz offers excellent value without sacrificing essential protection.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Evacuation strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Up to €1M evacuation coverage (usually sufficient)</li>
    <li>Partner assistance network</li>
    <li>Air ambulance included</li>
    <li>Repatriation covered</li>
    <li>15-20% cheaper than competitors</li>
    <li>Good coordination for standard evacuations</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>€1M limit (vs unlimited)</li>
    <li>Partner network may be slower in remote areas</li>
    <li>Family transport more limited</li>
    <li>Not ideal for very high-risk locations</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Expats in Europe, Latin America, mainstream Asia destinations. Cost-conscious expats who still want good evacuation. Those in moderate-risk locations.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Evacuation Coverage"
    description="Get quotes with evacuation benefits explained. Consider your location's risk level."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="evacuation-types">Types of Evacuation Coverage</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={evacuationTypesColumns} rows={evacuationTypesRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Medical Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    Transport to the nearest appropriate medical facility when local care is inadequate. This could mean a helicopter to a regional hospital or a medical jet to Singapore/Dubai for specialized treatment. All three insurers cover this.
  </p>

  <h3>Repatriation</h3>
  <p>
    Transport back to your home country for ongoing treatment or recovery. Often includes medical escort if needed. All three cover this, typically after initial stabilization.
  </p>

  <h3>Security/Political Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    Evacuation due to war, terrorism, civil unrest, or natural disaster—NOT medical. This is typically an add-on costing $100-300/year extra. Essential for high-risk countries. All three offer it as an option.
  </p>

  <h3>Mortal Remains Repatriation</h3>
  <p>
    If the worst happens, coverage for returning remains to home country. Costs $10,000-25,000 without insurance. All three include this.
  </p>

  <h2 id="when-needed">When Evacuation Coverage Matters Most</h2>

  <h3>High-Risk Locations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Africa (outside major cities):</strong> Essential—limited local facilities</li>
    <li><strong>Remote Asia:</strong> Important—may need evacuation to Singapore/Bangkok</li>
    <li><strong>Developing countries:</strong> Critical for serious conditions</li>
    <li><strong>Conflict zones:</strong> Security + medical evacuation needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Moderate-Risk Locations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Latin America major cities:</strong> Good local care, evacuation for complex cases</li>
    <li><strong>Southeast Asia hubs:</strong> Excellent local care, evacuation rarely needed</li>
    <li><strong>Middle East cities:</strong> World-class care, evacuation for home preference</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Low-Risk Locations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Western Europe:</strong> Excellent care, rarely need evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>Singapore/Hong Kong:</strong> World-class care locally</li>
    <li><strong>Japan/South Korea:</strong> Top facilities, language may drive repatriation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Live in or frequently travel to remote/high-risk areas</li>
        <li>Work in Africa or developing countries</li>
        <li>Want the fastest evacuation response</li>
        <li>Need security evacuation coverage</li>
        <li>Value direct (not outsourced) assistance</li>
        <li>Are willing to pay premium for best protection</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want premium service during any crisis</li>
        <li>Value excellent customer support</li>
        <li>Are in moderate-risk locations</li>
        <li>Want lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions to protect</li>
        <li>Prefer premium positioning</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Live in lower-risk destinations (Europe, developed Asia)</li>
        <li>Want good evacuation at better prices</li>
        <li>€1M evacuation limit is sufficient</li>
        <li>Prioritize value over premium features</li>
        <li>Are unlikely to need complex evacuations</li>
        <li>Want mental health benefits included</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>What triggers a medical evacuation?</h3>
  <p>
    Your insurer's medical team (with your treating doctor) decides if local care is inadequate for your condition. Common triggers: need for specialist surgery not available locally, ICU care unavailable, serious trauma requiring advanced facilities.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I choose where I'm evacuated to?</h3>
  <p>
    Generally no—the insurer determines the nearest appropriate facility. However, for repatriation (after stabilization), you can typically choose to go home. You can't demand evacuation to a specific country for preference alone.
  </p>

  <h3>Is €1M evacuation coverage enough?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually yes. Most evacuations cost $50,000-200,000. Complex international air ambulance with medical team rarely exceeds €500,000. The €1M limit covers almost all realistic scenarios. Unlimited is extra peace of mind.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need security evacuation?</h3>
  <p>
    If you're in potentially unstable countries, yes. It's cheap ($100-300/year) and covers evacuation for war, civil unrest, terrorism, or natural disaster. Medical evacuation does NOT cover these scenarios—they're separate.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I'm unconscious—who decides?</h3>
  <p>
    Your emergency contact (designated on your policy) and the insurer's medical team make decisions on your behalf. Keep your emergency contact info current and share your policy details with family.
  </p>

  <h3>Does evacuation cover a family member traveling with me?</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna and Bupa typically cover transport for one accompanying family member. Allianz may have limitations. Check your specific policy. This helps ensure you're not alone during a medical crisis abroad.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Evacuation coverage terms vary by plan and location. Some destinations may have exclusions (war zones, sanctioned countries). Verify your specific policy's evacuation terms and exclusions before relying on this coverage.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
